This data, while small, shows some interesting conclusions:

1. Data wise, actual content is a small part of the page
2. If you don't have a 60mpbs, wired connection, you could be waiting a long time for ads
3. Brave seems to have an edge up on uBlock Origin. Makes sense, as Brave has lower level access (browser vs plugin)
4. Brave Ads and Brave, No Ads seem to have nearly indistinguishable load times. This could be because all ads are still being blocked - Brave [doesn't replace every ad](https://brave.com/FAQ.html), or due to the faster ad selection process (described in the podcast).

As for rendering, games, and that sort of thing, Brave uses the same engine as Chrome, [Chromium](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chromium_(web_browser)).
Like Chrome and Firefox, [Brave is open source](https://github.com/brave).
